# Logging

Use the centralized logging from `utils/logging`:

```python
from utils.logging import get_logger

logger = get_logger(__name__)

logger.info("Message with %s", variable)    # General status
logger.debug("Details: %s", data)           # Verbose debugging  
logger.warning("Potential issue: %s", msg)  # Something to watch
logger.error("Failed: %s", error)           # Something went wrong
```

- Always use `get_logger(__name__)` at module level
- Use `%s` formatting, not f-strings (for lazy evaluation)
- No `print()` statements - use `logger.debug()` instead

